body:
I think I've figured out the problem.  In the http/2 upgrade, we upgrade the http/1.1 message to http/2

```
InboundHttpToHttp2Adapter.handle(ctx, connection(), decoder().frameListener(), upgrade.upgradeRequest().retain());
```

However, I don't think the h2c upgrade message, which is an http/1.1 message with the upgrade:h2c header, should not be eligible for flow control.  The spec isn't super clear here however.

@normanmaurer @Scottmitch @ejona86 any idea what we should do here?  Or a workaround I can apply in the mean time?
